at vendors I frequent (not that I could probably afford them if they were).<br><br>Also, was wondering if there was a handy-dandy list somewhere of the trivial levels for various spells? I can find the trivials for the Concordance of Research items, but I don't see anything hinting about how skilled I should be before attempting actual spells.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ellywig</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Thanks in advance for any help... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukolanistormynytes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KolaniStormynytes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/8/02 12:37:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Magician Spell Research</span><hr size=1> /wave<br><br>I think I looted some of those last night in Mistmoore, Elly. I think I still have shark skins too! Let me check my bank account and get back to you. I hate going to the bank, because the banker always harasses me about all the body parts I keep in there. I mean, you never know when you might need a dark elf heart or and orc head.... <p>Kolani - <center><A Href="http://www.geocities.com/kelethinlegions" target="new"><img src="http://www.boomspeed.com/kelelegions/kolanibanner.jpg" border="0"></A></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/9/02 8:16:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Magician Spell Research</span><hr size=1> My banker just keeps giving me odd looks about the stacks of rat meat. But hey, I will have skill in cooking AND some stacks of rat kabob appetizers to take along to the next language faire, if all goes well. I know you are all thrilled at the prospect.<br><br>What in Mistmoore (if you remember) drops this sort of stuff? I will gladly trade for any of these things that others have as spare (if I can find anything you want), but also looking for hints as to what sorts of things I should be whacking. Well, other than the obvious sharks, eh? That would be a no-brainer, I guess.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ellywig</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>WTB/WTT for clue cards! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uerazor983.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Erazor983</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/12/02 3:08:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Magician Spell Research</span><hr size=1> Ellywig,<br><br>Disregard if you like, but for any aspiring magician research is the worst.  Take some time to work up your skill using the Concordance of Reaserch to make practice runes.  The items needed to make the practice runes are much more available and/or cheaper to get than the actual spell research components.  Also, PUT EVERY LAST PRACTICE POINT INTO IT, I can't stress that enough.  This skill is hell to raise for a magician because our components tend to be rare (I've only ever had one Aviak feather at a time *shrug*).  You'll thank me when you can no longer buy your pet spells.<br><br>P.S.  Just failed my 39 earth pet a few days ago, ack more words of convocation please....<br><br>Trallos Drachen<br>Magi of the 39 Thousandth Summoning<br>Marshall of Ring of the Light  FV<br><br>&quot;Dispenser of useless items...Pez anyone?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/12/02 3:50:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Magician Spell Research</span><hr size=1> I've been saving practice points - have 40 in the practice bank right now to put towards research. And I know I can buy all my level 16 and 20 spells, but if I can try making some, maybe I can get a few more points in research before I absolutely have to have it. I plan on trying to get my hands on Concordance of Research stuff, too... but most of that seems a bit easier to find (thus I didn't ask about how to find rusty weapons or batwings or whatever). I had heard magician research was hell, so I am trying to think ahead a bit. Or am I already in the hole because I spent <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> any</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> practice points at all on other skills?<br><br>Which brings up that question again - is there a handy listing somewhere of what the trivials/recommended skill levels are for various levels of research spells? I'd like to minimize my impending poverty as much as possible...<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ellywig</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>At least I don't need to buy food... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uerazor983.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Erazor983</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/12/02 8:34:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Magician Spell Research</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://mythiran.allakhazam.com/">mythiran.allakhazam.com/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>Has all the trivials for Concordance of Research runes  up to 95.  Does not list the actual spell trivials though sadly.<br><br>And don't sweat any points you put in anything else, I blew 30 to 40 learning a good chunk of Old Erudian and Elvish plus every other language at least one point.<br><br>Trallos Drachen<br>Magi of the 39 Thousandth Summoning<br>Marshall of Ring of the Light<br><br>&quot;Dispenser of useless items....Pez anyone?&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uerazor983.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Erazor983</A> at: 4/12/02 8:38:51 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/13/02 12:36:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=59.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Magician Spell Research</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I saw the trivials for the Concordance runes... I was hoping I was just blind and missed the list of trivials for actual spells somewhere. *sigh*<br><br>Well, Wuggan did tell me that the life of a magician was a hard one... guess he wasn't joking, eh?<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ellywig</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Kobold Missionary Bait <p></p>